<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="921" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d921">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7698a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Parker</persName>, representing American
                                interests</hi><note n="1" xml:id="d921fn1">Same to American Consuls
                                at Guadalajara, Monterey, Tampico, Vera Cruz, Acapulco, Hermosillo,
                                Mazatlan, Manzanillo, Salina Cruz, Frontera and Progreso.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-15">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 15, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Scott-Obregon conference amicably concluded, but without definite
                                result.<note n="2" xml:id="d921fn2">
                                <hi rend="italic">See</hi> Political Affairs, ante, <ref target="#pg_527">p. 527</ref>
                                <hi rend="italic">et seq.</hi>
                            </note> Both Governments continuing negotiations. Surface indications do
                            not presage any untoward incident. You should be extremely alert,
                            however, to guard yourself and Americans, your district, against sudden
                            hostile developments.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>